<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="9" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="9">Diagnostic characters.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="9">
Amongst the southern African species, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Weim. ex Hilliard &amp; B. L. Burtt in Notes Roy. Bot. Gard., Edinburgh 43 (3): 347" authorityYear="1986" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cynoglossum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cynoglossum austroafricanum" order="Boraginales" pageId="0" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="austroafricanum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="9">Cynoglossum austroafricanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be confused with either 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="9">
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="C." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="C. lanceolatum" order="Boraginales" pageId="0" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lanceolatum">C. lanceolatum</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="C." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="C. coeruleum subsp. var. var. mannii" order="Boraginales" pageId="0" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="coeruleum" subSpecies="var." variety="mannii">C. coeruleum var. mannii</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
. This species differs from the two by the colour of the corolla (white corolla with pale blue throat vs pale blue corolla throughout in 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="C." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="C. austroafricanum" order="Boraginales" pageId="0" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="austroafricanum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="9">C. austroafricanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). This latter observation was also noted by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hilliard, OM" journalOrPublisher="Notes from the Royal Botanic Garden Edinburgh" pageId="0" pageNumber="9" pagination="345 - 405" publicationUrl="https://agris.fao.org/agris-search/search.do?recordID=GB19790370487" refId="B14" refString="Hilliard, OM, Burtt, BL, 1986. Notes on some plants of southern Africa chiefly from Natal: XLIII. Notes from the Royal Botanic Garden Edinburgh 43 (3): 345 - 405, https://agris.fao.org/agris-search/search.do?recordID=GB19790370487" title="Notes on some plants of southern Africa chiefly from Natal: XLIII." url="https://agris.fao.org/agris-search/search.do?recordID=GB19790370487" volume="43" year="1986">Hilliard and Burtt (1986)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="9" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="9">Distribution and habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="9">
The species is distributed in South Africa (North-West, Gauteng, Mpumalanga, Free-State, KwaZulu-Natal, and Eastern Cape Provinces), eSwatini and Lesotho (Figure 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Known distribution of Cynoglossum austroafricanum in southern Africa based on the specimens examined." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.193.72270.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/658892" pageId="0" pageNumber="9">8</figureCitation>
), where it occurs in shady, disturbed areas, and sandy, dry riverbanks.
</paragraph>
<caption doi="10.3897/phytokeys.193.72270.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/658892" pageId="0" pageNumber="9" start="Figure 8" startId="F8">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="9">Figure 8.</emphasis>
Known distribution of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Weim. ex Hilliard &amp; B. L. Burtt in Notes Roy. Bot. Gard., Edinburgh 43 (3): 347" authorityYear="1986" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cynoglossum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cynoglossum austroafricanum" order="Boraginales" pageId="0" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="austroafricanum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="9">Cynoglossum austroafricanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in southern Africa based on the specimens examined.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
